          <div style="margin: 2rem 0; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border); padding-left: 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem;">
            <div>
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
                <span style="width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-teal); color: white; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 700; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">1</span>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Capture</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="prose-ki">
                <p>Information arrives without immediate judgment. The Harbour receives everything — email, notes, links, conversations — before the Library decides what belongs. The principle here is separation: receiving is not the same as deciding.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
                <span style="width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-ocean); color: white; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 700; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">2</span>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Connect</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="prose-ki">
                <p>Material is contextualised and linked to existing knowledge. This is the transformation step — where received information becomes owned knowledge. Links form. Meaning emerges. A Stream becomes a Pillar note.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
                <span style="width: 2rem; height: 2rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-forest); color: white; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 700; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;">3</span>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Reflect</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="prose-ki">
                <p>Periodic review surfaces what's stale, updates what's changed, and retires what's obsolete. Reflection is not optional — it is how the island stays honest about what it knows. Without it, islands accumulate archaeology rather than knowledge.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

